Aim for in-between SA2 and Unleashed.

No boost or spin dash, you set a set ammount of speed at the start of the stage and are able to gain speed be abusing momentum

Tracks should vary on all 3 dimentions, hella turns, and ways to go up and down in the stage

Drifting:
	Drift arc changes based on how fast ur going, fast = bigger swing

Drop Dash:
	Converts vertical momentum into horizontal momentum, has the potential to lose speed if you just abuse it

Tricking:
	Basically just acts as a way to get extra air time, if you spam it you start to lose horizontal speed

Light Speed Dash:
	Completely converts your mommentum based on ring trail direction

Homing Attack (Aim to make it feel smoother):
	Triggers Attacking Flag and slightly increase momentum but don't ever lose it
	Have some enemys you cant kill, for example have the player react by having options like sliding

Rolling:
	Gain speed if going down hill lose speed if not.
	Gain Extra Speed if u Drop Dash into it

Stomping:
	Just a reaction and knowlege check.
	Maybe cancelable into Drop Dash

2D Sections (Think Generations): 
	Bounding Box based trigger system
	Should be overly short if done right
	Should barely even be platforming just basic reaction checks like sliding and jumping to bounce off enemys to go on paths

Style System:
	Scales the top speed by style ranks
	Gain Style by killing enemys and dodging without losing momentum, if you stop to kill shit thats lame

Rails:
	More or less just transitions
	Gain momentum by leaning with the curves, or just dont, you only get punished if you attempt and fail

General Notes On How To Feel Fast Asf:
	Scale Fov Based on Speed
	Hella Motion Blur
	Have The Camera Be Close To Sonic
	Make Track Lengths Slightly Shorter Than You Think To Have Less Reaction Time
	U Make The Game Dawg, Have The Nigga Out run the Camera at times

Enemys:
	Just cus you go fast doesnt mean ur safe (issue i noted in generations)
	In generations/unleashed if you had boost enemys werent shit
	Make Enemys A Part Of The Stage (Secret Paths if you homing attack in a certain Direction)
